main event: On May 19, 1960, a round object with projections was observed in Dillingham, Alaska, for approximately 5 hours.
interesting points: The object was described as being about the size of an automobile., Witnesses reported seeing the object come within 200 feet of them., Upon ascending, the object made a sucking noise and could lift lightweight items., Several natives observed and sketched the sighting, showing consistency in their drawings., The report classified the object as probably a weather balloon, but left many questions unanswered.
